\f0\fs24 \cf0 cc26xx-web-demo XSS bug - A persistent XSS vulnerability present in the MQTT/IBM Cloud Config page featured as part of the cc26xx-web-demo. The web demo contains much of Contiki\'92s core functionality, and the counterpart MQTT configuration page allows the user to remotely configure a device\'92s settings by sending HTTP POST requests. This vulnerability consists of inadequate input sanitisation of text fields on the MQTT/IBM Cloud config page. As a result, this allows for Javascript injection. \
